Olive Oil
1 packet pork loin steaks
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 courgette
1 bunch broccolini
½ lemon
1 packet garlic paste
1 packet Roasted Potatoes with Garlic Herb Butter
1 packet creamy pesto dressing

In a bowl, combine spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil. Add pork and toss to coat.
Heat olive oil in a large frying pan over medium-high heat.
Cook pork until cooked through, 3-4 mins each side.
Transfer to a plate to rest.

Meanwhile, thinly slice courgette.
Trim and halve broccolini lengthways.
Slice lemon into wedges.
Return pan to medium-high heat with olive oil.
Cook courgette, broccolini and garlic paste until tender, 4-5 mins.
Add lemon juice and season.

Poke a few holes in potato packet and microwave until hot and steaming, 3 mins.
Plate up pork, garlic greens and potatoes.
Serve with pesto dressing and lemon wedges.